Dessa, along with Topper and Fisk, has managed a daring landing onto the flying island of Astaroth, where she hopes to find her long-lost brother. Instead, they discover a bizarre world where three children are being held by a mysterious and rarely seen man they call the Toymaker. Meanwhile, Captain Drake has unintentionally stumbled upon Jared himself and decides to hold the boy as bait to lure Dessa to him. But why would such powerful people want to abduct a small peasant boy? Available in softcover and hardcover editions.
name: Book Six: The Dark Island

description:
Cinema can be done without electricity! That's what Fourmille and Yuri discover when they go to Hollywood to sign up the renowned super star Norma Jean to their Agency.

But when she is found dead, is it murder or suicide?

With Fourmille assuming the persona of Norma Jean, she must solve the mystery and find the true explanation of Norma's death!
name: Hollywood Boulevard

description:
Many years ago, Buxton Stonebeard was banished from his dwarven home amid a shower of blood. But his cursed axe demands a soul, and so the outcast must return. Accompanied by Skarlok, his unlikely Morkai ally, and Niobe, a budding hero, Buxton must save the town that condemned him.

Femforce #174 is now available! Old and new friends abound in this 80-page blockbuster (as are ALL issues of FF these days) chronicling the adventures of comicdom’s first (and best) all-female super-team. Inside a dramatic Dell Barras cover, it starts off right away with the 31-page lead story “Rock Aria”. In the wake of the tragedy at Roberta Stock’s almost-wedding (last issue), the FF return to an emergency call from founding member RIO RITA that leads to a trip to Brazil to investigate a mysterious, hulking destructive force appearing in the Amazon jungle. Is it a terrible NEW menace? Yes-AND no. It’s ZAZURRA, the living stone giantess that actually debuted in AC’s Big ‘Uns #2, back many years ago, but who has never previously appeared in the FF universe. She’s here now, and it’ll be up to Ms. VICTORY, SHE-CAT, SYNN and TARA to deal with. Throw in a sprinkling of Dr. Carlos Jimenez and his Time Triangle, Lady Luger and Fritz Voltzmann, and it’s another Stephanie and Mark Heike, Rock Baker and Jeff Austin triumph. Then, RAD is back taking the next step on her journey toward respectability as she moves forward in her secret undercover assignment infiltrating the dangerous paramilitary subversive group The Strong Hand, in “Stepping Into The Twilight Zone”, written by Mark Heike, with art by Baker and Austin. SYNN ends up as a contestant on a game show in an offbeat solo adventure in “A Girl With Brains”, from the mind of writer Mark Holmes with pencils by Dan Gorman and inks by Scott Shriver. Penciler Dan Gorman returns to handle art duties on “The Final Days of Sirius Quinn”. TARA FREMONT investigates the abandoned jungle research facility of a recently-deceased scientist only to find a very unusual situation. Written by UK sensation Andrew Hawnt, and inked by the versatile Scott Shriver. Everybodies’ favorite reluctant heroine, YANKEE GIRL is back to deal with a deadly tropical threat at the Arctic Circle(?) in “Ice Age Baby”, written by Mark Holmes, with pencils and inks by Riccardo Desini. Finally, as a special flip-book feature, long-time AC artist Dan Gorman and his collaborator Joseph A. Michael have created an all-new superheroine that has caught on as an online sensation- The ATOMIC BLONDE!! She makes her FIRST in-print appearance here in FF #174 in an adventure set in a 1940’s World War II world just SLIGHTLY different than our own, entitled “Enter The AquaNazis!!”. We think FEMFORCE readers will love it. Add it all up and it comes out to be 80 full pages of 100% ALL-NEW, never-before-seen story and art in the great AC tradition of “good girl” art and action.

The team's new recruit doesn't get much time to settle in, as the team is called to stop a new villain, the impossible Doctor Vector! Also, tension begins to build between the team and the company in the midst of the scandal.

In the mid-1930s, Irmina, an ambitious young German, travels to London. There she meets Howard Green, one of the first black students at Oxford. Like Irmina, Green is looking for an independent existence - and a love affair blossoms between two outsiders. But the relationship comes to an abrupt end when Irmina, constrained by the political situation in Hitler's Germany, has to return to Berlin. Political events accelerate, and her letters to Howard are returned unopened. It will be 30 years until she receives another. Based on a true story, this moving and perceptive graphic novel conjures the oppressive atmosphere of wartime Germany and reflects on the passive complicity of its people with sympathy and intelligence.
name: GN

description:
Meet the World's Greatest Con Artists on the eve of the greatest scam in human history --ripping off the Gods themselves! The high-stakes, high-octane story of JACKPOT! begins here! Ray Fawkes, acclaimed creator of INTERSECT (writer of Gotham by Midnight and Batman: Eternal) teams up with Marco Failla (Spider-Man & the X-Men) to bring a new mind-bending, genre-busting monthly series from AfterShock!

name: The Players

description: How does Alyss Heart of Wonderland fare after the creation of Everqueen, as described in ArchEnemy, the third volume of the best-selling The Looking Glass Wars trilogy? With difficulty. Fending off political assaults from rival suit families, struggling to maintain diplomatic relations with the tribes of Boarderland, Alyss is more vulnerable than ever before. After she barely escapes an attempt on her life, no longer sure whom to trust, she aligns with controversial new allies in order to keep Wondertropolis safe and prevent havoc on Earth. And yet the fight, the battle, finds her - as it seemingly always does - and Alyss discovers that all decisions, even the right ones, have consequences.
name: Volume 6

description: The iconoclastic and bestselling cartoonist of Paying for It returns with a polemical interpretation of the Bible that will be one of the most controversial and talked-about graphic novels of 2016. Mary Wept over the Feet of Jesus is the retelling in comics form of nine biblical stories that present Chester Brown's fascinating and startling thesis about biblical representations of prostitution. Brown weaves a connecting line between Bathsheba, Ruth, Rahab, Tamar, Mary of Bethany, and the Virgin Mother and reassesses the Christian moral code by examining the cultural implications of the Bible's representations of sex work.
name: GN

volume.name: Mary Wept Over the Feet of Jesus

description: Every nation that invades the City gives it a new name. But before long, new invaders arrive and the City changes hands (and names) once again. The natives don't let themselves get caught up in the unending wars. To them, their home is the Nameless City, and those who try to name it are forever outsiders. Kaidu is one such outsider. He's a Dao born and bred--a member of the latest occupying nation. Rat is a native of the Nameless City. At first, she hates Kai for everything he stands for, but his love of his new home may be the one thing that can bring these two unlikely friends together. Let's hope so, because the fate of the Nameless City rests in their hands. Available in softcover and hardcover editions.
name: GN

description: The image of Samia Yusuf Omar running for last place at the 2008 Beijing Olympics will forever be imprinted in the minds of all who saw it: The lean Somalian, wearing knee-length leggings and a baggy T-shirt, came in seconds behind her competitors. What the cheering crowd couldn't know then was what it took to get there. An Olympic Dream follows Omar's second attempt to represent her country at the Olympics, this time in London. By telling the story of one remarkable woman, Kleist gives voice to the thousands of migrants who risk their lives daily for a better future.
name: GN

volume.name: An Olympic Dream: The Story of Samia Yusuf Omar

description: Feeling better and ready to rebuild her public image, Plus Ultra takes the day off. Unfortunately, a militant activist group called the Blood of the Earth interrupts her plans. Will the new Plus Ultra shine in her first public appearance, or will it be back to the drawing board?

The Outriders have stolen a volatile piece of Star Sheriff tech, leaving Saber Rider and the bounty hunter Colt to form an uneasy alliance. Outriders expert April Eagle is on the scene, but is it already too late? The classic '80s animated series is back in this wild western/sci-fi mashup!

volume.name: Saber Rider and the Star Sheriffs

description: With their problems behind them, everything slowly returns to “normal” for Hector and his daughter. But their moment of peace is about to come to an abrupt end as someone comes back into their lives. Someone Hector thought he'd never see again.

Follow Apple again, one of the central characters of Turbo Kid, in an action packed prequel! Are you ready to go deeper into the universe of this already cult movie? Face the Robots War and the path that led Apple on the Kid's route!

You’ll find more action than you know what to do with! In the latest part of ‘Superheavy,’ the new Batman, Jim Gordon, continues his fight against the deadly Mr Bloom. In Robin, Son of Batman, Damian faces someone he thought dead, and in Batman Eternal, Alfred makes a horrifying discovery!

It’s time for some serious Batman action! In this issue, you can see the new Batman, Jim Gordon, going up against the deadly Mr. Bloom, plus in Batman Eternal, the original Batman Bruce Wayne faces the Architect and make a shocking discovery! Plus, there’s the latest instalment of Damian’s ‘Year of Blood’!

It’s time for some serious Batman action! You’ll find three action-packed stories inside, including the new Batman battling Mr Bloom, and the amnesiac Bruce Wayne revisiting Wayne Manor! Meanwhile, in Batman Eternal, Catwoman gets embroiled in gang warfare!

Welcome to the latest issue of Batman! We have 100 pages of Bat action in store for you, including the new Batman, Jim Gordon, facing Mr. Bloom! Meanwhile, Damian’s ‘Year of Blood’ continues, Bruce Wayne finds himself in a madhouse, and in Batman Eternal, Stephanie Brown goes into action as the Spoiler!

Welcome to the 50th issue of Batman! Yes, we’ve reached our half-century of issues! Inside, you’ll find three thrilling stories about the Dark Knight. First up, there’s the latest instalment of ‘Superheavy,’ in which Bruce Wayne wants some answers! Next up is a special one-off story where Batman faces a double, before we round things up with Batman Eternal, where Batmantries to track down Hush!

Batman – ‘Superheavy' – Part 9’

Inspired by recent events, Bruce Wayne realizes who he really is, and insists on gaining entry to the Batcave. But even if Alfred lets him in, is he prepared for what he’ll find? And how far will Bruce go to reclaim his identity as the Batman?

Batman Eternal – ‘City of Whispers’

As riots break out across Gotham City, Batman and his new assistant Julia Pennyworth try to keep things under control. Meanwhile, the rest of the Bat family do their bit to keep order on the streets, but Commissioner Jason Bard has his own ideas on how to take back control!

The endgame of Grant Morrison’s epic Batman saga, one that he has been telling since ‘Batman and Son’, way back in Batman Legends #1, begins this issue, with an event both shocing and tragic. We won’t say any more here – just star reading! After a double dose of BATMAN INCOROPORATED, it’s time to check in with Harper Row. Can she save Batman… again?

Batman Incorporated – Belly of the Whale

Talia al Ghul looks unstoppable. With the teeth of Leviathan sunk deep into the flesh of Gotham, Batman and his allies have nowhere left to turn…

First printed in Batman Incorporated #7

Batman Incorporated – The Boy Wonder Returns

…it now falls to Bruce Wayne’s only son, Damian, to save the day… and to prove to his mother that he is a hero – and not the terror he was grown to be!

First printed in Batman Incorporated #8

Batman – Resolve

The aftermath…

First printed in Batman #18

Joker has been planning this issue’s psychological terror for over a year, and now it’s time for Scott Snyder and Greg Capullo to show you how it all goes down! Who dies? And, after it all… can the Batman Family survive? Meanwhile, Damian Wayne tries to get closer to his father, by making Bruce retrace the steps that made him Batman – and taking over the cowl in his absence. Can Gotham take this Batman’s heat? Find out this issue!

Batman – Death of the Family: The Punchline

It’s all come down to this, as Joker has Batman and all of his allies bound and helpless… and he’s serving them terror for dinner!

First printed in Batman #17

Batman Impossible

As part of a plan to get closer to his father, Damian Wayne has sent Bruce on a global scavenger hunt, picking up the pieces of his history, and of what made him into the Batman. Meanwhile, he’s using his father’s absence to show him how Batman should be done!

First printed in Batman and Robin Annual #1

We hope that you’re fans of nail-biting tension, jaw-dropping shocks and mind-blowing surprises, readers, because that’s all we’ve got between this issue! It’s the penultimate chapter of Scott Snyder and Greg Capullo’s Joker epic, and things are getting criminally weird up in Arkham Asylum. Meanwhile, Grant Morrison and Chris Burnham blow the doors off in an unforgettable pair of BATMAN INCORPORATED episodes!

BATMAN – Death of the Family: Castle of Cards

Lured into Arkham Asylum, Batman must face off against his oldest foe – and his gallery of rogues – in the dark heart of madness!

BATMAN INCORPORATED – Asylum

At last, Bruce Wayne tells Damian of the apocalyptic vision of the future he saw as he was hurled through time (see ‘The Return of Bruce Wayne’ for the full scoop!). Its time for more Batman 666 – as Gotham ends!

BATMAN INCORPORATED – Garland of Skulls

Back in the present, the Batman Incorporated saga takes some more shocking twists! Hold onto your hats as we speed towards the finale at a thousand miles per hour!

It’s an action-packed issue of Batman: Arkham! In Arkham Unhinged, when Batman is unavailable to battle a deadly gang, the mysterious Azrael steps in, but can he be trusted? Meanwhile, in Detective Comics, Batman must try and escape the seemingly perfect world of ‘Gothtopia.’ But as the Scarecrow doeses him with his latest toxin, what hope is there? And finally, in Batman: The Dark Knight, the Caped Crusader must use all his ingenuity to capture the slippery Clayface!

There’s a whole lot of newness in this issue of Batman Arkham! In Arkham Unhinged, Batman comes face-to-face with Gotham City’s newest crimefighter, Azrael! Then, in Detective Comics, there’s a new beginning, with a new creative team, a new villain, and a new drug on the streets that’s set to tear Gotham apart. Can Batman do anything to stop it? Meanwhile, in Batman: The Dark Knight, you can witness the origin of the shape-changing Clayface!

In this issue of Batman Arkham, the Caped Crusader gets entangled with the dangerously seductive Talia Al Ghul in Batman: Arkham Unhinged. Then he has problems of a different kind in Detective Comics, as the war on the streets over the drug Icarus takes another deadly turn. Meanwhile, in Batman: the Dark Knight, the ‘Voiceless’ arc continues as a mute Batman takes on a slavery ring with a familiar face behind it.

In Batman: Arkham Unhinged, stately Wayne Manor comes under attack, and with Batman out of the way, who’s going to defend it? In Detective Comics, meanwhile, the ‘Icarus’ storyline comes to an end with a truly incendiary final chapter! Last but by no means least, in Batman: The Dark Knight, Gotham’s sky is the hunting ground for a mystery menace! Could the Man-Bat be back?

It’s an all-action issue, as we open with Batman: Arkham Unhinged, when Wayne Manor is under attack and Alfred, Robin and Nightwing have to defend it, before Batman must track down the mysterious Bookbinder! Then, it’s the start of a new storyline in Detective Comics, as Batman faces death and potential chaos at Gotham International Airport in ‘Terminal!’ In Batman: The Dark Knight meanwhile, Batman tangles with the newer and even more fearsome Man-Bat!

It’s another all-out issue for Batman, as he tracks the mysterious Bookbinder in Arkham Unhingedand battles a deadly biological attack in the conclusion of ‘Terminal!’ And we introduce a new strip – Gotham Central, the inspiration for the hit show Gotham!

Things aren’t easy for Batman in this issue, as a curfew causes chaos in Arkham Unhinged, and a brand new threat, ‘Anarky,’ begins in Detective Comics! In Gotham Central meanwhile, the GCPD need help to find Mister Freeze!

Batman has his work cut out for him in this issue of Batman Arkham,not least when he faces the Bookbinder in Arkham Unhinged! In Detective Comics the mysterious Anarky continues to wreak havoc, while in Gotham Central, the city’s police force face a fiery threat!

You want Batman action? We’ve got it for you! The deadly Bookbinder continues to evade the Dark Knight in the latest installment of Arkham Unhinged! It’s the show-stopping finale to ‘Anarky’ as Batman tries to stop the influential villain, while in Gotham Central, the cops try to stop their city being engulfed in flames!
